{"id":26869274453,"name":"Test","node_id":"WFR_kwLOA_1uaM8AAAAGQYiXVQ","head_branch":"perf/users-perf-test-isolate-scenarios","head_sha":"e34d7b8c0d6d6ede33be32183e4e76804c718090","path":".github/workflows/run-tests.yml","run_number":53947,"run_attempt":1,"event":"pull_request","display_title":"perf: isolate UsersPerformanceTest scenarios and reuse session","status":"completed","conclusion":"success","workflow_id":10954,"check_suite_id":72086792165,"check_suite_node_id":"CS_kwDOA_1uaM8AAAAQyLUn5Q","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/26869274453","html_url":"https://github.com/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/26869274453","pull_requests":[{"id":3793441996,"number":24107,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/pulls/24107","head":{"ref":"perf/users-perf-test-isolate-scenarios","sha":"e94f93f40d3c43a2825bb21ac9a6558dd2279863","repo":{"id":66940520,"name":"dhis2-core","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core"}},"base":{"ref":"master","sha":"5a1b89baf57c3f7563c2c12de21f5f9777b3d6b0","repo":{"id":66940520,"name":"dhis2-core","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core"}}}],"created_at":"2026-06-03T07:06:33Z","updated_at":"2026-06-03T07:14:59Z","run_started_at":"2026-06-03T07:06:33Z","jobs_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/26869274453/jobs","logs_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/26869274453/logs","check_suite_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/check-suites/72086792165","artifacts_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/26869274453/artifacts","cancel_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/26869274453/cancel","rerun_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/26869274453/rerun","head_commit":{"message":"perf: isolate UsersPerformanceTest scenarios and reuse session\n\nThe \"GET User - by uid\" p95 assertion kept failing on CI (e.g. 783ms vs\n700ms) while the endpoint is ~10-14ms locally. The latency was not the\nendpoint; it was an artifact of how the test measured:\n\n- `.basicAuth()` on the protocol sent the Authorization header on every\n  request, forcing a full bcrypt password verification each time (~70ms,\n  ~88% of measured time) with no auth-result cache.\n- Default `mode=parallel` ran all 7 scenarios concurrently, cramming the\n  bcrypt-heavy work into a short burst that starved the single shared\n  self-hosted CI runner. Faster multi-core dev machines hide this.\n- Only ~10-20 samples per scenario made p95 a coin flip, so repeatedly\n  bumping the threshold did not stop the flapping.\n\nChanges:\n- Default `mode` to `sequential` so each scenario is measured in isolation\n  (single-endpoint latency). `parallel` remains available as an opt-in\n  mixed-load stress mode.\n- Authenticate once per virtual user and reuse the JSESSIONID cookie\n  instead of re-authenticating on every request. The login request is\n  named separately so its bcrypt cost is excluded from per-endpoint\n  assertions. Relies on CSRF being disabled (the DHIS2 default).\n- Bump iterations (load 10-\u003e30, smoke 3-\u003e10) for a more stable p95.\n\nVerified locally (profile=load, iterations=30): 248/248 OK, GET p95\n783ms -\u003e 20ms, write scenarios succeed under session-cookie auth.\n\nThresholds were calibrated under the old regime and are now far too loose;\nthey are flagged in-code as pending recalibration from fresh nightly\nbaselines.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e","author":{"name":"Jason Pickering","email":"jason@dhis2.org"},"id":"e34d7b8c0d6d6ede33be32183e4e76804c718090","tree_id":"00772e8558853b0c5ab7dd9ef43a246d501790fd","timestamp":"2026-06-03T07:06:05Z","committer":{"name":"Jason Pickering","email":"jason@dhis2.org"}},"workflow_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/workflows/10954","repository":{"id":66940520,"node_id":"MDEwOlJlcG9zaXRvcnk2Njk0MDUyMA==","owner